==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ethylsulphuric
<hw>Eth`yl*sul*phu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or containing, ethyl and
sulphuric acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ethylsulphuric acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an
acid sulphate of ethyl, <chform>H.C2H5.SO4</chform>, produced as a thick
liquid by the action of sulphiric acid on alcohol. It appears to be the
active catalytic agent in the process of etherification.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etiolate</ent>⟦br⟧
